x4freetext: Self-supporting Ni target of thickness 150 mu-g/cm**2.
nine independent detection arms comprising various
kinds of detectors. Two of these arms (placed at 15.
and 120. angles in respect to the beam direction) are
equipped with the Bragg curve detectors (BCD), which
permit the Z- identification of the reaction products
and determination of their kinetic energies with low
The active volume of BCD`s has thickness of 22 cm of
isobutane at a pressure of 206 mbar.
*By authors*.The absolute normalization of the cross
sections was achieved by comparing the total production
cross sections of Be-7 particles, obtained by angle and
energy integration of measured differential cross
sections, with values of Be-7 total production cross
sections published in the compilation of Bubak et al.
